Package common

Interface Message

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    public interface Message
extends java.io.Serializable
    The Interface Message. Defines a behavior of transferable object through the network. It contains only constants (server protocol) and methods to get required data once received.

    • Method Detail

      • command

        int command()
        Command to (or from) the server. For example, if it is LOGIN, then server tries to login the user and if success, it sends Message with this command back to the sender along with the unique token (see token()).
        Returns:
        the command constant

      • file

        byte[] file()
        File to specify xml data for billboard to be displayed.

        the byte[]

      • token

        java.lang.String token()
        Token - unique session identifier between server and client (control panel).
        Returns:
        the string representation of token

      • permission

        java.lang.String permission()
        Permission as a string (see Permission). Server sends permission after LOGIN to identify what the user is able to do (edit, add, delete etc.). To get permission, server refers to database (table 'user', attribute 'permission').
        Returns:
        the string representation of permission

      • users
